<section id="changing-perspectives" version="5.0" xmlns="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"
                                                  xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude"
                                                  xmlns:xl="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" >
  <title>Changing perspectives</title>
  <orderedlist>
    <listitem>
      <para>
        To change between perspectives, select:
        
        <para>
          <emphasis role="menupath">Window</emphasis>--&gt;<emphasis role="menupath">Open Perspective</emphasis>.
        </para>
      </para>
    </listitem>
    <listitem>
      <para>
        Select which perspective to open.
      </para>
    </listitem>
    <listitem>
      <para>
        Alternatively, you can use the icons in the top left-hand
        corner of the current perspective to toggle between
        perspectives.
      </para>
    </listitem>
  </orderedlist>
  <section id="automatically-changing-perspective">
    <title>Automatically changing perspective</title>
    <para>
      By selecting:
      
      <para>
        <emphasis role="menupath">Window</emphasis>--&gt;<emphasis role="menupath">Preferences</emphasis>,
      </para>
      
      you can choose to automatically change to the Execution Perspective when test execution starts, or to be asked each time a Test Suite is started.
    </para>
  </section>
</section>